Title: Es falso el mensaje que alerta que comercios de Veracruz cerrarán por coronavirus

Summary: A Whatsapp message circulated in Mexico spreading out-of-context or misleading information on the likely trends in the epidemiological curve (the peak lasts 15 days) and on the meaning of the R_0 parameter

Minister of Justice and Public Security, Sergio Moro, then cited this case (acknowledging it needed to be confirmed) at a press conference, using it to argue that detainees shouldn't be released indiscriminately due to COVID. It turns out the detainee had finished serving his sentence, and was not released due to the pandemic.

Narrative_Description: Costa Rican Health Minister, Daniel Salas, announced resignation amid pandemic
Motive_Description: Spread false info. about resignation of a political figure
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Daniel Salas, resignation, Health Minister
Summary: A chain of Whatsapp messages falsely spread that Costa Rican Health Minister Daniel Salas announced his resignation amid covid-19 pandemic.

Title: #NoComaCuento: Costa Rica no se encuentra en la ‘etapa máxima de infección’ del covid-19
Narrative_Description: Costa Rica has reached its "maximum stage of infection" of covid-19
Motive_Description: Stoke fear over severity of the virus
Key_Words: Coronavirus, maximum infection stage, peak, virus transmission
Summary: Several messages spread via Whatsapp and Facebook claiming that Costa Rica would experience its peak of covid-19 cases between March 23 and April 3, comparing the country's situation to that of Italy in its first weeks of covid-19 case reporting. Health authorities clarified this is erroneous

Title: #NoComaCuento: Es falso que este miércoles entra a regir un toque de queda por 14 días en Costa Rica
Narrative_Description: A 14 day curfew will begin on April 1st
Motive_Description: Spread false info. about government measures
Key_Words: Coronavirus, curfew, April 1, Costa Rica
Summary: An audio message spread via Whatsapp claiming that a 14 day curfew would be imposed in Costa Rica beginning on Wednesday, April 1st.

Title: #NoComaCuento: No habrá un ‘apagón’ mundial del Internet durante Semana Santa
Narrative_Description: There will be a global Internet "blackout" during Easter week, during which mass arrests will be made
Motive_Description: Create fears about massive communications "blackout" and mass arrests
Key_Words: Coronavirus, global blackout, Internet, mass arrests, Easter
Summary: An image shared via Whatsapp and Facebook spread that a global "blackout" of Internet networks would occur for 3 days leading up to Good Friday, and that during this worldwide "blackout" mass arrests would be made.

Title: #NoComaCuento: Auto Mercado no está regalando cupones de $500, ni Papa John’s pizzas por pandemia de covid-19
Narrative_Description: Auto Mercado is giving away $500 coupons and Papa John's is giving away 2 large pizzas to each family during the pandemic
Motive_Description: Phishing scam
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Papa Johns, Auto Mercado, $500 coupon, pizza
Summary: Several mesages spread via Whatsapp and Facebook claimed that Auto Mercado, supermarket chain in Costa Rica, was giving away $500 coupons and that Papa John's was giving away 2 large pizzas to each family during the pandemic.

Title: Certificación de Inciensa que circula en redes habla de cantidad de pruebas y no de casos positivos de COVID-19
Narrative_Description: Certification from Inciensa claims there are 855 positive cases of Covid-19 in Costa Rica as of April 13th
Motive_Description: Uncertain
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Inciensa, 855 positive cases, tests
Summary: A Facebook page published erroneous information that Inciensa, a Costa Rican Institute for Research, claimed that there were 855 positive cases of Covid-19 in the counry as of April 13th. In actuality, the document released by Inciensa showed the laboratory had processed 855 tests that had tested positive, but this did not equate to the number of people tested due to repeat testing and other variables.

Title: #Verificamos: Es antigua la foto de baile funk que habría incumplido la cuarentena de la Covid-19
Narrative_Description: Funk concert during the lockdown
Motive_Description: Spread fear of contagion
Key_Words: Coronavirus, funk, dance, concert, Brazil, lockdown
Summary: Old picture circulated claiming to show a funk concert/dance in Brazil during the lockdown.

Title: Ainda não existe cura para coronavírus; auto-hemoterapia não tem comprovação e pode ser perigosa
Narrative_Description: Autohemotherapy cures coronavirus
Motive_Description: Reference to new cure/preventative measure
Key_Words: Coronavirus, autohemotherapy, cure, prevent, Brazil
Summary: False claim circulated that autohemotherapy (injecting one's blood in one's muscles) is an effective cure/preventative measure against coronavirus.

Title: #NoComaCuento: Imagen divulga información falsa sobre fechas de depósitos del bono Proteger
Narrative_Description: Protect bonus deposits will be made based on ID numbers of their certificates
Motive_Description: Mistaken interpretation of procedure of deposits
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Protect bonus, ID number, dates
Summary: An image spread via Whatsapp claiming that the time at which recipients of the Proteger bonus in Costa Rica would receive aid depended on the ID number assigned to them. In actuality, the bonus is received based on the date that each beneficiary's aid was deposited for the first time.

Title: Detector: Ni el primer ministro de Italia dijo que perdió la batalla contra el Covid-19 ni es la persona que aparece en ésta foto
Narrative_Description: Italian PM said the country has lost the battle against coronavirus
Motive_Description: Spread fear of the pandemic
Source_Description: Facebook account Giovanny Higuera, website Remedios Natural Hosting
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Italian, Prime Minister, Giuseppe Conte, lost, battle, Bolsonaro
Summary: Picture of Bolsonaro circulated in Colombia claiming it was Italian PM Giuseppe Conte who had said that Italy has lost its battle against coronavirus.

Title: #NoComaCuento: Es falso que la prueba de covid-19 puede causar infección en el cerebro y la muerte
Narrative_Description: Text claiming that covid-19 tests can cause infections, inflammation, and death
Motive_Description: Spread fear over covid-19 testing
Key_Words: Coronavrus, swab, blood-brain barrier, infection, inflammation, death
Summary: Text circulated social media claiming that covid-19 swabs took samples from the blood-brain barrier, and that the tests could introduce bacteria and toxins to the brain through contact with the blood-brain barrier, leading to possible inflamation of the brain, infections, and death.

Title: No hay un casos sospechoso de Covid-19 en Colcapirhua
Narrative_Description: Suspect case in Colcapirhua, Bolivia
Motive_Description: Spread fear of contagion
Key_Words: Coronavirus, suspect, case, Bolivia, Colcapirhua, hospital
Summary: Fake chain message circulated in Bolivia claiming that a suspect patient was hospitalized in Colcapirhua.

Title: ES FALSO QUE A LOS FAMILIARES DE PERSONAS CON COVID-19 “SOLO LES AVISARÁN QUE MURIÓ”
Narrative_Description: Claim that minors with covid-19 are taken from their parents and not allowed to say goodbye if they pass away
Motive_Description: Spread fear about process to treat minors infected with covid-19
Key_Words: Coronavirus, minors, relatives, goodbye, isolation, treatment
Summary: An image circulated social networks detailing an incorrect process of treating minors infected with covid-19 in Guatemala. The post included claims that infected minors are taken away from their parents, cannot say goodbye if they die, and that relatives will not be allowed to attend a funeral.

Title: ES IMPRECISO DECIR QUE LA BANCADA SEMILLA VOTÓ EN CONTRA DE LA LEY DE EMERGENCIA POR LA COVID-19
Narrative_Description: Claim that the Semilla Movement's Congressional bench voted against the Covid-19 Emergency Law
Motive_Description: Discredit the Semilla Movement political party
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Semilla Movement, Emergency Law, Congress, absent
Summary: False claims spread via social media that, because a few Semilla Movment members withdrew from a congressional session when representatives voted in favor of a Covid-19 Emergency Law, the Semilla Movement's bench as a whole had voted against the law. However, four members of the bench were present and voted in favor.

Title: ¡BULO! // J. RODAS NO SOLICITÓ QUE LAS PRUEBAS DE COVID-19 SEAN PAGADAS POR LA CIUDADANÍA
Narrative_Description: Claim that judge and notary Jordán Rodas Andrade demaded that covid-19 tests be paid for by citizens
Motive_Description: Spread false info. about political figure
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Nación Libre Gt, Jordán Rodas Andrade, tests, citizens, paid
Summary: A facebook profile spread fake information that Human Rights Ombudsman, Jordán Rodas Andrade, demanded that covid-19 tests be paid for by the citizens.

Title: ¡BULO! // “PLAN REACTIVACIÓN ECONÓMICA DE GUATEMALA”
Narrative_Description: False economic recovery plan for Guatemala
Motive_Description: Provides hope-inducing timeline for economic and social recovery
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Economic Recovery Plan, phases, Guatemala
Summary: Posts circulated social media detailing the phases of an alleged economic recovery plan for Guatemala

Title: MINISTERIO DE SALUD ASEGURA QUE NO HAY COLONIAS CON CORDÓN SANITARIO EN CIUDAD DE GUATEMALA
Narrative_Description: Speculation about a sanitary cordon in Guatemla City
Motive_Description: Creates fear about community cases necessitating a sanitary cordon in Guatemala city
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Sanitary Cordon, Guatemala City, community cases
Summary: Speculation led to a mention on Twitter in which someone questioned whether there was a sanitary cordon implemented by the Ministry of Health in Guatemala City.

Title: ¡BULO! // CACIF NIEGA HABER CONVOCADO PARA CARAVANA EN EL OBELISCO
Narrative_Description: A claim to reject the total closure of the country was falsely attributed to Cacif (the Coordinating Committee of Agricultural, Commercial, Industrial and Financial Associations
Motive_Description: Target Cacif through falsely attributed political statement
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Cacif, total closure, caravan
Summary: An image spread via social media falsely attributed a call for the "rejection of the total closure of the country and the State of Public Calamity" to Cacif, the Coordinating Committee of Agricultural, Commercial, Industrial and Financial Associations.

Title: NO, NO CERRARÁN LOS HOSPITALES TEMPORALES
Narrative_Description: False claim that Juan Nájera, director of the Quetzaltenango Health Area, said that temporary hospitals will stop treating covid-19 patients
Motive_Description: Create fear over closing of temporary hospitals
Key_Words: Coronavirus, temporary hospitals, close, Quetzaltenango, Juan Nájera
Summary: Hoax spread via Facebook that the director of the Quetzaltenango Health Area said that temporary hospitals, which are used to care for covid-19 patients, will stop treating those patients and/or close.

Title: VERDADERO // GIAMMATTEI SÍ FUE AL HOSPITAL, PERO A UN CHEQUEO
Narrative_Description: False claims that Guatemlan President, Alejandro Giammattei, was admitted in an emergency to a hospital due to a delicate state of health
Motive_Description: False reporting of video that surfaced
Source_Description: Coronavirus Guatemala, An0nymous Guatemala, and A Diario GT Twitter accounts
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Giammattei, emergency, admitted, hospital
Summary: Two Twitter accounts falsely claimed that Guatemalan President, Alejandro Giammattei, had been admitted in an emergency to a hospital due to being in a delcate state of health; based this off of a video of his car parked otuside of a hospital during a general medical check-up.

Title: QUÉ SABEMOS DEL VIDEO DE UN ENTIERRO SIN CADÁVER EN SOLOLÁ
Narrative_Description: A coffin arrived empty at a funeral in Sololá
Motive_Description: Misunderstanding of situation and video contents
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Sololá, coffin, empty, funeral
Summary: A video circulated Twitter and Facebook spreading that the coffin of a deceased young man arrived empty at his funeral.

Title: La pérdida de olfato y gusto, ¿son síntomas del Covid-19?
Narrative_Description: Smell and taste loss are approved symptoms of coronavirus
Motive_Description: Spread handy tip to detect coronavirus
Source_Description: Psychiatrist José Miguel Gaona, general public
Key_Words: Coronavirus, symptoms, smell, taste, José Miguel Gaona
Summary: Psychiatrist José Miguel Gaona misleadingly said in a video that smell and taste loss are symptoms of coronavirus, although this information was not approved by either the Bolivian Health Ministry nor the WHO.

Title: Video de una persona con problemas respiratorios no es de Bolivia, sino de Colombia
Narrative_Description: Person with breathing problems is positive to covid
Motive_Description: Spread scary video of consequences of coronavirus.
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Bolivia, hospital, Santa Cruz, breathing, problem
Summary: Video (really from Colombia and showing a preson who tested negative for coronavirus) circulated in Bolivia claiming it showed a person with coronavirus experiencing difficulty in breathing.

Title: Circula video de campaña, bono y COVID-19
Narrative_Description: Political ad advertizing a relief program
Motive_Description: Discredit the Juntos movement and its leader Mario Cavero.
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Bolivia, Bs.500, Juntos, Mario Cavero, video, ad
Summary: An ad promoting a government sponsored bonus circulated in Bolivia and was attributed to the Juntos movement and its leader Mario Cavero, so to discredit them for politicizing the promotion of the relief program.

Title: FALSO que en NL se haya instruido Ley Seca por COVID-19
Narrative_Description: The Mexican State of Nuevo León prohibited the sale and consumption of alcoholic beverages.
Motive_Description: Spread fake claim on emergency measures
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Mexico, Nuevo León, Ley Seca, alcohol, beverages, sell, consume, ban
Summary: Doctored screenshot of news article circulated in Mexico claiming that the State of Nuevo León had passed a "Ley Seca", that is a ban on sales and consumption of alcoholic beverages in response to the ensuing pandemic.

Title: Detector: No hay estudio que certifique que el coronavirus dura cuatro minutos en el calor
Narrative_Description: The virus does not survive more than four minutes from the heat
Motive_Description: Spread fake claim to argue that the virus is not invincible
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Soares, four minutes, heat
Summary: In an interview, the famous Brazilian virologist Gubio Soares, claimed that the virus cannot survive more than 4 minutes the heat. However, the WHO did not confirm this.

Title: Hola Mónica...': el audio viral de una supuesta sanitaria que habla de 'pacientes jóvenes, sin patología, que 'van a morir' por coronavirus en la Fundación Jiménez Díaz
Narrative_Description: Young patients are dying at the Jimenez Diaz Foundation since they ran out of beds for intensive care
Motive_Description: Spread fake audio to spark fear among people

Summary: An audio on WhatsApp was spread saying that at the Jimenez Diaz Foundation in Spain young patients are dying without symptoms since they ran out of beds for intensive care.

Title: No, el diario brasileño Folha de S. Paulo no ha anunciado el positivo en coronavirus del presidente Jair Bolsonaro: es una cuenta fake de Twitter que ya ha borrado
Narrative_Description: Jair Bolsonaro was found positive to the virus
Motive_Description: Spread the news by mistake
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Folha de S. Paulo, Bolsonaro, positive
Summary: The Twitter account of TVPerù Noticias reported that the Brazilian media outlet Folha de S. Paulo reported that Bolsonaro has been found positive to the virus. However, it was not true that Folha did that. It was a mistake by TVPerù

Title: #NoComaCuento: Es falso que cuerpos de muertos por covid-19 no se le entregan a los familiares

Title: Es FALSO que no hay que salir «ni por el pan»

Title: “El número de nuevos contagiados [de Covid-19] está reduciéndose desde el día 19 [de marzo]”
Narrative_Description: Cases have been decreasing in Peru
Motive_Description: Corroborate her own argument
Source_Description: María Isabel León, president of the Confederación Nacional de Instituciones Empresariales Privadas (Confiep)
Key_Words: Coronavirus, peru, Confederación Nacional de Instituciones Empresariales Privadas, Confiep, María Isabel León, cases, universities
Summary: When asked her opinion about reducing college fees while the coronavirus emergency lasts, María Isabel León, president of the Confederación Nacional de Instituciones Empresariales Privadas (Confiep) from Peru, said that it made no sense as cases had been steadily decreasing in the country, an untrue assertion as of March 24, 2020.

Title: No, el Ejército no ha sacado “un tanque” por la calles de Tudela para combatir el COVID-19

Summary: Picture of a tank (taken from a different context) circulated in Spain claiming it showed a effort by the army in the town of Tudela to contain the spread of the virus.

Title: El Mundo no ha publicado que Andalucía haya “puesto sobre la mesa” repetir el curso escolar
Narrative_Description: The Andalucian local government is considering making students repeat the school year
Motive_Description: Spread fear of emergency measures
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Andalucía, El Mundo, repeat, school year
Summary: Doctored screenshot of an article by Spanish newspaper El Mundo circulated claiming that the region of Andalucia is considering having students repeat the school year due to the coronavirus pandemic.

Title: No, 'El País' no ha publicado que Juan Carlos I ha dado positivo en la prueba de coronavirus: es un tuit falso
Narrative_Description: El Paìs said that Juan Carlos I, the former king of Spain, has been found positive to the virus

Key_Words: Coronavirus, El Paìs, Juan Carlos I, positive
Summary: A Twitter account looking like El Paìs wrote that Juan Carlos I, the former king of Spain, has been found positive to the virus. However, it was not true that the newspaper has published the news and that tests results were out. They were still waiting for results

Title: Circula falso tuit de la presidenta sobre coronavirus
Narrative_Description: A tweey by the president of Bolivia Jeanine Añez saying that the situation is under control and electoral campaigns should continue
Motive_Description: Target Bolivian president Jeanine Añez by undermining her way of reacting to the emergency
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Jeanine Añez, electoral campaigns, control
Summary: A false tweet by the president of Bolivia Jeanine Añez in which she said that the situation is under control and electoral campaigns should continue as usual. However, the tweet was a fake one.

Title: Falso: no hay muertos confirmados por coronavirus
Narrative_Description: A tweet allegedly by the secretary of the Health Department, Oscar Urenda, saying that a woman died because of the virus
Motive_Description: Spark fear by saying that some people died because of the virus
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Oscar Urenda, dead, woman
Summary: A tweet claimed that the Oscar Urenda, the secretary of the Health Department, said that one of the first patients of Covid-19 in Bolivia died. However, none of these two things was true.

Title: Coronavirus: La Red Uno no publicó esta información sobre asambleísta del MAS
Narrative_Description: A story saying that the assemblyman Edwin Muñoz of the Socialist Movement said that Covid-19 is a punishment against the people because they did not support Evo Morales
Motive_Description: Discredit assemblyman Edwin Muñoz
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Edwin Muñoz, assemblyman, punishment, support
Summary: A Facebook post claimed that assemblyman Edwin Muñoz, of the Socialist Movement, claimed that Covid-19 is a punishment to the people of Bolivia because they did not support Evo Morales. The post claimed the news was published by Red Uno. Neither of these two things was true.

Title: #Verificamos: La foto de los bañistas en Copacabana no fue tomada ‘durante la cuarentena’
Narrative_Description: People gathered on the beach in Copacabana
Motive_Description: Spread fear of contagion
Key_Words: Coronavirus, beach, Copacabana, gathering
Summary: Picture of a crowded Copacabana beach circulated online alongside the claim it showed the place during the lockdown.

Title: Esta política española no hizo declaraciones sobre Messi, ni Ronaldo, ni la cura del coronavirus
Narrative_Description: Spanish scientist said Messi and Ronaldo should find the cure to coronavirus, given how much more they're paid compared to scientists

Source_Description: Facebook accounts Somos Partido Anticorrupcion - PAC, Nayeli Magali, Fútbol Internacional, Vi Sama, Mexicanos al grito de guerra, Madre,Abuela,Tierra,Cuantica, Y deja tu lo guapx, soy Biólogx, عماد متعب Emad Meteb, Soccer Memes, Roberta Petoilho, Twitter accounts @fjsv1974, @3mrojito, Instagram accounts santiagomatiasgarciass, coronavirusargentina_oficial, augusto_tw, Wykop.pl account ropppson
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Spanish, scientist, pay, Messi, Ronaldo, cure, Isabel García Tejerina.
Summary: A picture (actually showing Spanish politician Isabel García Tejerina) circulated alongside claims it showed a Spanish scientist who said Messi and Ronaldo should find the cure to coronavirus, given how much more they're paid compared to scientists

Title: La mujer fue detenida por discutir con empleados y el video muestra dos incidentes diferentes
Narrative_Description: Woman tests positive for coronavirus and then spits on fruits at the supermarket
Motive_Description: Stoke anger against Chinese people
Source_Description: Facebook accounts Alexis Alejandro Rivas, Claudio Rizzi, Luis Tomas Gago, Policias de Honor, Leinara Isaia, Roberto Rodriguez, Indians all over the world, Twitter accounts @ceciliaponce, @tdexx22, @HoLainYu, YouTube channel AMARILIS NADALES, PunishedJohnMcClane
Key_Words: Coronavirus, woman, Asian, positive, spit, fruit, supermarket, Australia
Summary: A video (actually mad up of two different videos) circulated claiming to show an Asian woman in Australia who, after testing positive for coronavirus, is caught spitting on fruits at the supermarket.

Title: La imagen es del entierro de una legisladora iraní contagiada con el coronavirus
Narrative_Description: Picture shows a coronavirus victim in Italy
Motive_Description: Mistake
Source_Description: Facebook accounts Gioga Garcia Baquero, Noticiero Paracentral (online news media), l tiempo de Dios es perfecto, Plataformas Cochabamba, Jose Reza, Llallagua - Noticias
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Italy, Iran, Fatemeh Rahbar, dead
Summary: A picture of the body of Iranian MP Fatemeh Rahbar being carried after she died due to coronavirus was associated to (correct) news on Italy.

Title: No dejan sin respiradores a los ingresados con coronavirus mayores de 65 años
Narrative_Description: Doctors in Spain are quitting ventilators from elderly people to give them to the younger ones.
Motive_Description: Spread fear of consequences of the virus
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Spain, doctors, ventilators, elderly, young, quit
Summary: A video of a self-described doctor circulated in Spain claiming that ventilators are being taken away from elderly people to give them to younger ones, due to their scarcity.

Title: Detector: No, un estudio no reveló que el humo del cigarrillo puede transportar el nuevo coronavirus
Narrative_Description: The smoke coming out of cigarettes can carry the virus
Motive_Description: Spread fear of getting virus from smokers
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Colombia, Clarín Internacional, smoke, cigarette, carry, virus
Summary: Online news website Clarín Internacional published an article in which it claimed that the smoke coming out of cigarettes is a potential carrier of coronavirus, misleadingly referring to a scholarly article which showed that smoking can reduce the capability of one's immune system to fight the infection.

Title: "Agente 1224" y otros productos milagro contra el coronavirus: no piques, no hay evidencias de que ningún aceite esencial cure el COVID-19
Narrative_Description: Essential oil "Agent 1224" cure coronavirus
Motive_Description: Make money out of sales
Key_Words: Coronavirus, oil, essential, Spain, Salud, Nutrición y Bienestar S.L, Agente 1224
Summary: Company Salud, Nutrición y Bienestar S.L sold an essential oil called "Agente 1224" claiming that it cured coronavirus.

Title: El bulo de la disolución de las Cortes por los positivos en coronavirus del Presidente y los tres vicepresidentes del Gobierno: no está prevista en la Constitución y sólo Carmen Calvo ha dado positivo
Narrative_Description: The President and all three vice presidents of Spain tested positive for coronavirus
Motive_Description: Discredit the incumbent government

Summary: Fake infographic circulated in Spain claiming that the Spanish PM Oedro Sanchez and his vice presidents all tested positive for coronavirus, a situation in which the Spanish constitution purportedly calls for the king to dissolve both the parliament and "the Courts" and set up new elections.

Title: ¿El coronavirus se adhiere a cremas, maquillaje y esmaltes?
Narrative_Description: The virus sticks to creams, make-up, nail polish, and jewelry
Motive_Description: Generate fear of possibly common source of contagion

Summary: Anonymous WhatsApp audio message (purportedly from an unidentified worker at the Gregorio Marañón Hospital in Madrid) circulated in Spain claiming that the virus sticks to nail polish, creams, make up, and jewelry.

Title: Es FALSO que China se preparó para la contención y dejó que la población se contagie
Narrative_Description: China let its people get infected and got ready to contain the spread of the virus later on
Motive_Description: Sow distrust towards China
Key_Words: Coronavirus, China, prepare, containment, contagion
Summary: Fake claim circukated in Paraguay about China allegedly letting its people get coronavirus and preparing for the containment.

Title: Es FALSO que no se están estudiando los contactos de los casos positivos de coronavirus
Narrative_Description: The government is not engaging in contact-tracing
Motive_Description: Discredit the incumbent government
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Paraguay, contact, tracing, government
Summary: Fake claim was spread in a WhatsApp voice message in Paraguay about the government supposedly not engaging in contact-tracing during the covid health emergency.

Title: Gobierno no ha aprobado despidos colectivos por Coronavirus
Narrative_Description: The government is allowing firms to engage in collective dismissals
Motive_Description: Discredit the incumbent government
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Colombia, government, firms, collective, dismissals
Summary: Fake claim circulated in Colombia that the government was allowing firms to engage in collective dismissals of workers during the coronavirus emergency.

Title: ¿Venezuela es el único país que tomó medidas adelantadas contra el COVID-19?
Narrative_Description: Venezuela has low case counts because it was the only Latin American countries to implement early containment measures
Motive_Description: Extol the incumbent administration

Summary: Fake claim circulated in Venezuela that German news channel DW had confirmend that the country had a low case count because it had been the first country in Latin America to implement early containment measures.

Title: ¿En África no hay coronavirus? Eso es falso, sí hay casos en ese continente
Narrative_Description: There are no cases in Africa since African countries don't have money to get indebted with the IMF
Motive_Description: Discredit the IMF
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Africa, debt, IMF, cases
Summary: Fake claim circulated about Africa supposedly not having coronavirus cases because it would not be convenient for the IMF, given that countries in the continent are poor and cannot get indebted with the Fund.

Title: FALSO | Propagandista del régimen miente al decir que el Covid-19 sólo contagia a “blancos y ricos”.
Narrative_Description: The virus only affects the rich and white
Motive_Description: Support Nicaragua's government action
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Nicaragua, William Grisgsby, ebola, white, rich
Summary: Nicaraguan propagandist William Grisgsby claimed that coronavirus is the "ebola of the white and rich", thus justifying the very lax measures taken by the goevrnment to contain the epidemic.

Title: La Universitat de Barcelona no aprobará a sus alumnos si las clases se suspenden durante más de un mes
Narrative_Description: The Universitat de Barcelona will have students pass all their classes if the latter get suspended for longer than a month
Motive_Description: Spread fake claim about university action
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Universitat de Barcelona, pass, classes, suspended, month
Summary: Fake screenshot from the Universitat de Barcelona website circulated in Spain with the claim that the university would have students pass all their classes if the latter were to be suspended for longer than a month.

Title: Cuidado con la campaña falsa de “contribución alimentaria” que usa el logo de la ONU: es un fraude
Narrative_Description: The UN is offering food aid
Motive_Description: Phishing
Key_Words: Coronavirus, UN, food aid, Colombia, link
Summary: Fake infographic circulated in Colombia claiming that the UN had instituted a campaign to deliver food assistance to people at home during the lockdown. The message contained a link most likely aimed at phishing.
Notes: Last from end of March, page 118 on the database

Title: Falso: El dióxido de cloro aún no está autorizado para combatir el coronavirus
Narrative_Description: The Bolivian government has approved the sale and use of chlorine dioxide
Motive_Description: Put out a catchy headline
Key_Words: Coronavirus, chlorine dioxide, approved, sale, use, Bolivia
Summary: Online news outlet RTP Bolivia published a note on its Facebook page claiming that the national authorities had approved the sale and use of chlorine dioxide, whereas the proposal was only passed in the Health Committee in the House of Representatives (Comisión de Salud de la Cámara de Diputados).

Title: No, esta imagen de la intro de Futurama en la que prohíbe viajar en el tiempo a 2020 no es real, es un montaje
Narrative_Description: Futurama scriptwriter had predicted the ongoing pandemic
Motive_Description: Spread conspiracies
Key_Words: Coronavirus, travel, ban, Futurama, 2020, Matt Groening
Summary: Doctored image taken from cartoon show Futurama in which the author Matt Groening put up the heading "ALL TIME TRAVEL TO THE YEAR 2020 IS STRICTLY PROHIBITED", thus predicting the ongoing pandemic.

Title: No, Pedro Sánchez no ha recomendado a los españoles invertir en Bitcoin Era para generar ingresos mientras dure la pandemia del coronavirus: es un timo
Narrative_Description: Spanish PM Pedro Sánchez recommended investing in Bitcoin during the pandemic
Motive_Description: Scam
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Spain, PM, Pedro Sánchez, invest, bitcoin
Summary: An article (disguised as by CNN) suggested that Spanish PM recommended investing in Bitcoin during the pandemic.

Title: No, el Comité Científico no es el mismo que el Comité Técnico para la Desescalada que decidió el paso de fases: el Comité Científico se creó el 21 de marzo y se reunía semanalmente
Narrative_Description: The Spanish government lied about the existence of a scientific committee in response to the coronavirus emergency
Motive_Description: Discredit the government (perhaps also confusion between two different committees played a role in the making of this piece of fake news)
Source_Description: Facebook page Asociación Forja Hispánica, other pages
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Spain, committee, scientific, deescalation, lie, deny
Summary: A fake claim circulated about the Spanish government having lied about the existence of a scientific committee in the middle of the health crisis. Although this narrative is for sure politically motivated, it originated from a tweet by PM Pedro Sánchez with which he announced the creation of a new, different technical committee in August. This is unrelated to the other scientific committee, which had been operative since late March.

Title: Cuidado con este vídeo difundido como si estuvieran haciendo pasar un maniquí por un paciente con coronavirus: es una simulación realizada en un tren medicalizado en Atocha (Madrid)
Narrative_Description: Video is shot so to hide that the patient is in reality a puppet
Motive_Description: Spread a fake claim
Source_Description: Facebook account Jorge Q-anon Trump, YouTube channel (not available)
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Spain, ambulance, hide, mannequin
Summary: A first aid simulation done in madrid was reported on video (done with a mannequin), alongside claims that who shot the video tried to hide the fact that they were using a mannequin and pretend they were treating a coronavirus patient.

Title: Tradujeron mal frase de Tedros sobre solución a la pandemia de COVID-19
Secondary_Country: Colombia, Spain, Argentina, Ecuador, Peru, Dominican Republic
Narrative_Description: The WHO said there is no solution to coronavirus and never there will be one
Motive_Description: Misunderstanding of Ghebreyesus's words
Source_Description: Online newspapers El Tiempo, El Periódico, La Nacion, El Universo, RPP Noticias, Listín Diario, Univisión, Infobae
Key_Words: Coronavirus, solution, silver bullet, WHO, Ghebreyesus
Summary: Many nespapers in Latin America spread the misleading claim that WHO President Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus said there is no solution for coronavirus and there will never be one (while he really said there is no silver bullet).

Title: No, esta foto no es de 500 pateras en Argelia a punto de zarpar rumbo a España con personas infectadas de COVID-19: es Mauritania en 2019 y son barcos de pesca
Narrative_Description: Boats full of infected people are ready to depart from Algeria to Spain
Motive_Description: Discredit immigrants
Key_Words: Coronavirus, immigrants, Algeria, Frontex, infected, Spain, depart
Summary: A picture (actually showing Fishing boats in Mauritania) circulated in Spain alongside the claim that it showed boats in Algeriafull of infected immigrants and ready to depart towards Spain.

Title: No, esta foto no es de la manifestación de Berlín contra las medidas de Alemania para frenar el coronavirus: es del festival 'Love Parade' de Berlín de 2003
Narrative_Description: People in Berlin marched against the anti-covid measures
Motive_Description: Encourage people to take action against anti-covid measures
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Berlin, Love Parade, march, protest, measures
Summary: A picture (actually showing the Love Parade in 2003 in Berlin) claimed to show people in Berlin marching as a sign of protest against the anti-covid measures taken by authorities.

Title: Cuidado con el vídeo que dice que la carpa del Hospital Arnau de Vilanova de Lleida es una "mentira": funciona como una sala de espera para pacientes con síntomas de COVID-19, no como un hospital de campaña
Narrative_Description: A tent installed outside an hospital is 'a lie' since it's empty
Motive_Description: Discredit health authorities
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Spain, tent, camp, empty, Hospital Universitario Arnau de Vilanova, Lleida
Summary: A picture of a tent outside the Hospital Universitario Arnau de Vilanova in Lleida, Spain (actually used to host patients while they wait for their test results) was spread around claiming it was proof that such "camp hospital" was a lie since the picture shows the tent was empty.

Title: Ministro de Gobierno da una cifra falsa sobre fallecidos en El Alto
Narrative_Description: 170 people died of coronavirus in three days in the city of El Alto
Motive_Description: Mistake
Source_Description: Minister of Government ('Ministro de Gobierno') Arturo Murillo
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Arturo Murillo, Boivia, El Alto, 170, cases, three, days
Summary: Bolivia's Minister of Government Arturo Murillo misleadingly claimed that 170 people had died in three days in the city of El Alto.

Title: Las recaídas del COVID-19 no se dan por consumir azúcar, tomar agua fría o bañarse por la noche
Narrative_Description: Relapse of coronavirus can happen if one eats sugar, drinks cold water or bathes at night
Motive_Description: Spread fear about possible sources of relapse
Key_Words: Coronavirus, relapse, sugar, cold, water, bath, night
Summary: Misleading WhatsApp chain circulated in Bolivia claiming that a relapse of coronavirus could happen if one eats sugar, drinks cold water, or bathes at night.

Title: No, este vídeo no muestra a un supuesto fallecido por COVID-19 levantando el brazo en Bolivia: lo que se ve en las imágenes es un simulacro
Narrative_Description: Video shows health workers dealing with actors rather than true bodies of victims
Motive_Description: Share funny video
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Spain, puppet, raise, arm
Summary: Video of health workers collecting dead bodies (although the video shows a simulation with a puppet) was shared claiming that an actor was used as the victim since the body raises its arm at one point.

Title: La Policía no puede allanar espacios privados en Medellín por incumplimiento de Ley Seca
Narrative_Description: The police in Medellin is authorized to enter people's houses to enforce the ban on alcohol consumption
Motive_Description: Instill fear of consequences
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Colombia, Daniel Quintero, Medellin, ley seca, enter, police, house, enforce
Summary: The mayor of Medellin Daniel Quintero claimed that the police would be authorized to enter people's houses to enforce the ley seca, banning to drink alcohol during the weekends,

Title: La imagen muestra un vehículo futurista, no una predicción de cómo sería el 2022
Narrative_Description: An Italian magazine had predicted the post-covid way of life in 1962
Motive_Description: Spread intriguing story about the ongoing pandemic having already been predicted
Source_Description: Facebook accounts Francisco Gago Nieto, ADN Cultura, Dionisio Pulido, Erik Camacho Garcia, Multimedia UPB, Sergio Donna, Mahendra Thami, Magno Gonçalves, Twitter accounts @IreneWais, @martinezmau, @UberCitizen, Instagram profiles gbp_sales_container, vuelodenoche.marta
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Italian, magazine, Domenica del Corriere, 2022, 1962, predict
Summary: An illustration from Italian Magazine "Domenica del Corriere" in 1962, which shows people moving on the street in glass capsules, was spread claiming that the magazine explicitly linked the drawing to how life would be in 2022, thus anticipating the coronavirus pandemic.

Title: No, la Policía de Berlín no ha tuiteado que asistieron 3,5 millones de personas a la manifestación contra las medidas de Alemania para combatir el coronavirus
Narrative_Description: Berlin's police tweeted that 3.5 million people participated in an anti-mask demonstration
Motive_Description: Push negationist theories
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Berlin, police, tweet, 3.5 million, demonstration
Summary: A fake screenshot of a tweet by Berlin's police containing the false claim that 3.5 million people took part in am anti-mask demonstration which really mobilized only about 17.000 people.

Title: #NoComaCuento: Ni OIJ ni Fuerza Pública reportan casos de ladrones disfrazados de médicos o enfermeros
Narrative_Description: Members of the Red Cross are exploting the pandemic to assault people at home
Motive_Description: Push fake story about members of the Red cross to target that institution and spread distrust toward it
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Red Cross, members, assaults
Summary: A fake story was pushed saying that doctors and nurses of the Red Cross are exploiting the pandemic to get into houses and assault people. This was done to spread distrust toward that institution

Title: País Vasco anunció el 12 de marzo la suspensión de clases, pero días antes se viralizó una captura falsa de El Correo cuando sólo se habían suspendido en Vitoria y Labastida*
Narrative_Description: Tweet saying that on March 12, schools will be closed across the whoile Basque country territory
Motive_Description: Push fake news probably by mistake
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Basque country, schools, closed
Summary: A fake news saying that schools are going to be closed since March 12 across the whole Basque country territory. This was a mistake since at that time, the measure had already been taken only for few schools.

Title: Kicillof: “En este momento [hay] cuarentena estricta en Barcelona”
Narrative_Description: Barcelona was in a strict lockdown at the end of July
Motive_Description: Mistake
Source_Description: Governor of the Province of Buenos Aires Axel Kicillof
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Buenos Aires, Axel Kicillof, lockdown, strict, Barcelona
Summary: Axel Kicillof, governor of the Province of Buenos Aires, claimed on July 31st that, among other cities in the world, Barcelona was subject to a strict lockdown (whereas the state of emergency had already been lifted by the Generalitat de Catalunya)

Title: #Verificamos: La OMS no dio marcha atrás y pasó a defender la “vuelta a la economía”
Narrative_Description: The WHO retreated on its previous statements and recommended reopening the economy
Motive_Description: Push anti-lockdown narrative
Key_Words: Coronavirus, WHO, retreat, recomment, open, economy, work
Summary: A fake claim circulated in Brazil about the WHO having retreated on their previous recommendations and suggesing that the economy should reopen and people get back to work.

Title: #Verificamos: La foto de “voluntario de vacuna china” que habría sufrido efectos colaterales es de 2017
Narrative_Description: Photo of Chinese nurse who experienced side effects from the coronavirus vaccine being tried on him
Motive_Description: Spread fear of possible side effects of vaccines in the course of being tested
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Coronavac, Chinese, nurse, side effects, Andrew Seely
Summary: A picture of a student who had been the victim of a prank in 2017 was shared in Brazil with the claim that it was a Chinese nurse who had experienced side effects from the coronavirus vaccine that had been tested on him.

Title: #Verificamos: Es falso que CoronaVac se produzca a partir de “células de bebés abortados”
Narrative_Description: Chinese vaccine is being developed using cells from aborted fetuses
Motive_Description: Discredit China
Key_Words: Coronavirus, vaccine, CoronaVac, China, cells, fetuses, aborted
Summary: Fake claim circulated in Brazil claiming that Chinese company Sinovac is producing its coronavirus vaccine (CoronaVac) using cells from aborted fetuses.

Title: Después de tomar ivermectina hay ciertas restricciones, pero no como advierten en las redes
Narrative_Description: After taking ivermectin, there are a few restrictions
Motive_Description: Spread fake claim, help
Key_Words: Coronavirus, ivermectin, restrictions, meat, fish, beverages
Summary: Fake claim circulated on WhatsApp about some restrictions, suhc as meat, fish, and beverages, after taking ivermectin (the latter being a treatment for coronavirus still under study).

Title: O material jornalístico produzido pelo Estadão é protegido por lei. As regras têm como objetivo proteger o investimento feito pelo Estadão na qualidade constante de seu jornalismo. Para compartilhar este conteúdo, utilize o link: https://politica.estadao.com.br/blogs/estadao-verifica/vacina-cubana-contra-coronavirus-e-ficcao/#Versao_em_espanhol
Narrative_Description: Story saying that the Cuban government already has a vaccine to be delivered to people
Motive_Description: Spread the news the Cuban government has already a vaccine to generate false hope among people
Key_Words: Coronavirus, vaccine, Cuba, ready
Summary: A fake claim circulated on social media saying that the Cuban government already has a vaccine ready to be delivered. Yet, the Cuban government has partnered with China to deliver the drug interferon alfa 2B to treat patients, but it does not have a vaccine yet.

Title: Detector: No, Min.Salud no ha enviado ningún correo informando sobre el coronavirus
Narrative_Description: A photo showing an email sent by the Ministry of Health informing citizens about the presence of the virus
Motive_Description: Spread fake photo to target the Colombian Ministry of Health
Key_Words: Coronavirus, email, Ministry of Health, informing
Summary: A fake photo showing an email sent by the Ministry of Health of Colombia to citizens and informing them of the presence of the virus. However, it was not true.

Title: Falso que personal de Salud realice pruebas de Covid-19 a domicilio
Narrative_Description: A story saying that the health workers are doing tests at people's houses and not in hospitals
Motive_Description: Spread fake news to undermine the credibility of the Health Department in Mexico
Key_Words: Coronavirus, tests, home, health workers
Summary: A fake chain of messages on WhatsApp claimed that in Mexico health workers are doing testing at people's houses and they are saying people shoudn't go to the hospital.

Title: ¿Evo con coronavirus?
Narrative_Description: A story saying that Evo Morales, the former president of Bolivia, got the virus
Motive_Description: Spread fake news to spark fear about the spread of the pandemic
Key_Words: Coronavirus, positive, Evo Morales, El Deber
Summary: A fake account of the newspaper El Deber tweeted that Evo Morales, the former president of Bolvia, tested positive to the virus. However, it was not true.

Title: En China no dieron por finalizada la epidemia del coronavirus; se han acumulado más de 80.000 casos
Narrative_Description: A story saying Chinese people are celebrating the end of the pandemic
Motive_Description: Spread fake news to generate false hope that the pandemic is over
Key_Words: Coronavirus, over, Chinese, celebration
Summary: A fake story was spread saying that Chinese people are celebrating the end of the pandemic. However, in China there were already 80,000 cases and the pandemic was not over.

Title: Es falso que un buen aseo bucal destruya el coronavirus o evite su contagio
Narrative_Description: Mouthwash and oral hygiene in general help prevent infection
Motive_Description: Help people
Source_Description: Peruan doctor Stalin Vílchez Rivera (on online news outlet El Correo), Facebook account Aníbal Cruz Llacsahuanga
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Stalin Vílchez Rivera, mouthwash, oral hygiene, Peru, doctor
Summary: Peruan doctor Stalin Vílchez Rivera falsely claimed that mouthwash and oral hygiene in general can prevent coronavirus infections.

Title: No, no hay un plan diseñado para el COVID-19 desde 2017 en documentos del Banco Mundial
Narrative_Description: World Bank website proves that Covid-19 is not new
Motive_Description: Conspire
Key_Words: Coronavirus, World Bank, WITIS, products, before
Summary: The World Bank changed the categorization of some products (that have been sold for years) on one of its databases to make them relevant in coronavirus-related searches. This was misleadingly used as proof that coronavirus had existed even before 2019 since coronavirus-related products have been traded for so long.

Title: No, esta foto de Pedro Sánchez supuestamente sonriendo durante sus vacaciones en Lanzarote no es actual: fue tomada en 2018
Narrative_Description: Spanish PM Pedro Sánchez is seen smiling and on vacation during the pandemic
Motive_Description: Discredit Pedro Sánchez
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Pedro Sánchez, vacation, Portugal, 2018
Summary: A picture of smiling Spanish PM Pedro Sánchez (actually taken in 2018) circulated alongside allegations that it showed him on vacation while the country was suffering from the pandemic.

Title: No, este vídeo no es de una manifestación contra el confinamiento en Aranda de Duero (Burgos): fue grabado en Barcelona
Narrative_Description: Anti-covid-restriction protest in Aranda de Duero
Motive_Description: Push anti-lockdown narrative
Key_Words: Coronavirus, Aranda de Duero, Spain, Barcelona, protest, lockdown
Summary: A video of anti-lockdown protests shot in Barcelona was spread on social media with the claim it showed protests in Aranda de Duero.

Title: O material jornalístico produzido pelo Estadão é protegido por lei. As regras têm como objetivo proteger o investimento feito pelo Estadão na qualidade constante de seu jornalismo. Narrative_Description: Story saying that a journalist in Lebanon wore a protective suit during the pandemic to spread panic
Motive_Description: Push anti-media narrative by saying they are trying to spread fear
Key_Words: Coronavirus, TV reporter, protective suit, panic
Summary: A post on Facebook was spread showing a TV report in Lebanon wearing a protective suit while working in order to spread fear among people. However, he was producing a story about a local protective clothing factory

Title: Según expertos, el “remedio” con saúco, jengibre, pimienta y miel que difundió el presidente de Venezuela no cura el COVID-19
Narrative_Description: Maduro and his followers spread a message containing a fake remedy against Covid-19 made by elderberry, ginger, pepper and honey
Motive_Description: Push a pro-regime narrative by showing the regime has found a good remedy against the virus
Key_Words: Coronavirus, remedy, Maduro, honey and ginger
Summary: A message was spread by some Venezuelan pro-regime users and by Maduro himself claiming that the regime has found the remedy against the virus, which is made of elderberry, ginger, pepper and honey
